rlVrrp.name: rlVrrp
rlVrrp.contactinfo: Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose , CA 95134-1706 USA Website: Cisco Small Business Home http://www.cisco.com/smb>;, Cisco Small Business Support Community <http://www.cisco.com/go/smallbizsupport>
rlVrrp.description: The private MIB module definition for VRRPv3 MIB.

rlVrrpv3OperationsTable.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsTable
rlVrrpv3OperationsTable.description: This table is parallel to vrrpv3OperationsTable, and is used to change VRRP on interface working version, description and display several statuses. It contains private objects.

rlVrrpv3OperationsEntry.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsEntry
rlVrrpv3OperationsEntry.description: An operation entry mapping for a particular interface.

rlVrrpv3OperationsDefaultPrimaryIpAddr.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsDefaultPrimaryIpAddr
rlVrrpv3OperationsDefaultPrimaryIpAddr.description: In the case where there are more than one IP Address (associated IP addresses) for a given `ifIndex', this object is used to specify the IP address that will become the vrrpv3OperationsMasterIpAddr', should the virtual router transition from backup state to master and no vrrpv3OperationsDefaultPrimaryIpAddr was configured.

rlVrrpv3OperationsPrimaryIpAddrState.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsPrimaryIpAddrState
rlVrrpv3OperationsPrimaryIpAddrState.description: This object represents enabled/disabled state of user configured primary address of the virtual router.

rlVrrpv3OperationsVrDescription.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsVrDescription
rlVrrpv3OperationsVrDescription.description: The description of the VRRP virtual router.

rlVrrpv3OperationsAdminState.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsAdminState
rlVrrpv3OperationsAdminState.description: This object will enable/disable the virtual router function. Setting the value to `up', will transition the state of the virtual router from `initialize' to `backup' or `master', depending on the value of `vrrpOperPriority'. Setting the value to `down', will transition the router from `master' or `backup' to `initialize'. State transitions may not be immediate; they sometimes depend on other factors, such as the interface (IF) state.

rlVrrpv3OperationsVrrpVersion.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsVrrpVersion
rlVrrpv3OperationsVrrpVersion.description: Current VRRP virtual router version it is working with.

rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterPriority.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterPriority
rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterPriority.description: This object specifies the priority which is used by master router.

rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterAdvInterval.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterAdvInterval
rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterAdvInterval.description: The time interval, in centiseconds, which is used by master router for sending advertisement messages.

rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterDownInterval.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterDownInterval
rlVrrpv3OperationsMasterDownInterval.description: Time interval for Backup to declare Master down (centiseconds).

rlVrrpv3OperationsSkewTime.name: rlVrrpv3OperationsSkewTime
rlVrrpv3OperationsSkewTime.description: Time to skew Master_Down_Interval in milliseconds.

rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrTable.name: rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrTable
rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrTable.description: This table is parallel to vrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrTable, and is used to display address statuses. It contains private objects.

rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrEntry.name: rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrEntry
rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrEntry.description: An entry in the table contains an IP address that is associated with a virtual router

rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrState.name: rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrState
rlVrrpv3AssociatedIpAddrState.description: This object represents state of the assosiated IP address, backed up by current virtual router.

rlVrrpv3CountersEntry.name: rlVrrpv3CountersEntry
rlVrrpv3CountersEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing statistics information about a given virtual router.

rlVrrpv3CountersChecksumErrors.name: rlVrrpv3CountersChecksumErrors
rlVrrpv3CountersChecksumErrors.description: The total number of checksum errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdPacketsLength.name: rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdPacketsLength
rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdPacketsLength.description: The total number of packet length errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersIpTtlErrors.name: rlVrrpv3CountersIpTtlErrors
rlVrrpv3CountersIpTtlErrors.description: The total number of TTL errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdInvalidTypePackets.name: rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdInvalidTypePackets
rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdInvalidTypePackets.description: The total number of invalid VRRP packet type errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdInvalidVrrpId.name: rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdInvalidVrrpId
rlVrrpv3CountersRcvdInvalidVrrpId.description: The total number of invalid VRRP id errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersProtoErrors.name: rlVrrpv3CountersProtoErrors
rlVrrpv3CountersProtoErrors.description: The total number of invalid VRRP protocol errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersAddressListErrors.name: rlVrrpv3CountersAddressListErrors
rlVrrpv3CountersAddressListErrors.description: The total number of invalid IP address list errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersAdvIntervalErrors.name: rlVrrpv3CountersAdvIntervalErrors
rlVrrpv3CountersAdvIntervalErrors.description: The total number of invalid advertisement interval errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersAuthErrors.name: rlVrrpv3CountersAuthErrors
rlVrrpv3CountersAuthErrors.description: The total number of authentication errors received on this interface. Counter is only valid as long as there is a VRRP router defined on this interface.

rlVrrpv3CountersRowStatus.name: rlVrrpv3CountersRowStatus
rlVrrpv3CountersRowStatus.description: Row status of the entry. Used for clearing table by setting.
